<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mandible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Anthessius graciliunguis Do &amp; Kajihara, female A habitus B urosome C left caudal ramus, dorsal D mandible, dorsal E area between inner seta and distal lash of mandible, ventral F maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C); 0.02 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720722" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2D, E</figureCitation>
) with bifurcate, rudimentary element on ventral side between bases of distal lash and inner seta; inner seta as long as distal lash. Maxilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Anthessius graciliunguis Do &amp; Kajihara, female A habitus B urosome C left caudal ramus, dorsal D mandible, dorsal E area between inner seta and distal lash of mandible, ventral F maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C); 0.02 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720722" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2F</figureCitation>
) consisting of syncoxa and basis; basis terminated in spiniform distal lash, armed with three setae (setae I-III); seta I (inner seta) small, rudimentary, positioned close to seta II; seta II simple; seta III minute, almost invisible; distal lash armed with five spines along convex outer margin and six spinules along inner margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Leg 4 with three spines and five setae on third exopodal segment. Leg 5 exopod 2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide.
</paragraph>
